title: Lissajous curve
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

A //Lissajous curve// is a curve of the form

$$\begin{pmatrix}
A \cos(at+a_0) \\
B \sin(bt+b_0)
\end{pmatrix}$$

with constants $$A,B,a,b,a_0,b_0.$$ It is [[closed|Closed curve]] if and only if $$a/b$$ is rational.